            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Coronary artery disease confirmed on imaging, management plan established</div>"
            },
            "code": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://loinc.org",
                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding our mutual patient, a 90-year-old male admitted on 03.06.2010 due to abnormal findings on cardiac imaging. Following admission, we performed a comprehensive diagnostic workup including resting ECG, echocardiography, and coronary CT angiography. These investigations confirmed the presence of significant coronary artery disease with multi-vessel involvement. Laboratory investigations revealed mildly elevated cardiac biomarkers without evidence of acute myocardial infarction. Given the patient's advanced age and overall clinical status, a conservative management strategy was agreed upon following interdisciplinary discussion. Optimal medical therapy was initiated, including antiplatelet therapy, statin, beta-blocker, and ACE inhibitor. The patient was discharged in stable condition on 04.06.2010. I kindly request continued monitoring of cardiac symptoms, medication compliance, and regular follow-up. Please do not hesitate to contact me for further information.</div>"
            },
